    {
      "level": "F",
      "levelType": "major",
      "text": "Topology",
      "children": [
        {
          "level": "1",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "General topology",
          "children": [
            {
              "level": "a",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Definition and basic concepts of topology; the subject matter and applications of topology as exemplified by certain simple topological problems and their solutions",
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "level": "b",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Topological spaces: methods for constructing topological spaces; Euclidean ^-dimensional space, Hilbert space, Cartesian-product space, and other examples of topological spaces",
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "level": "c",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Topological properties",
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "level": "d",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Topological problems of current interest; e.g., the planar fixed-point problem, the polyhedral Schoenflies problem",
              "children": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": "2",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "Topological groups and differential topology",
          "children": [
            {
              "level": "a",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Interaction between analysis and topology",
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "level": "b",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "The theorems of Tikhonov and Ascoli: embedding of a topological space as a subspace of a compact space",
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "level": "c",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Continuous groups",
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "level": "d",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Analysis on manifolds: topological implications of problems in global analysis",
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "level": "e",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Differential topology [see also C.6., above]",
              "children": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": "3",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "Algebraic topology [see also C.7., above]",
          "children": [
            {
              "level": "a",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "The nature and scope of algebraic topology and its context within general topology, the basic concepts of topological spaces and maps",
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "level": "b",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Invariants: unchanging quantities that play a central role in the classification of spaces and maps",
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "level": "c",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Homotopy theory: homotopy classes and the concept of homotopy-equivalent spaces",
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "level": "d",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Homology and cohomology theory: definition of a simplex, axiomatic homology theory",
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "level": "e",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Homotopy groups: stability and suspension",
